Class GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • treeview.GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    TREETYPE - The typeparemter for the GenericTreeElement. It is replaced with the specific type during instantiation of a concrete object.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GroupTreeNode, ItemTreeNode

    public class GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>
extends Object
implements ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
    Implementation of the ITreeNode interface. Basically each node of a tree has a specific data element (property) of a specific type ( TREETYPE) and contains a list of several sub-nodes (childs). The type of the children is always the same as the type of the current node. So in essence a tree can only consist out of elements from the same type. The type is determined during instantiation of a concrete object.
    Author:
    OOP

      • findItem

        public <T> ITreeNode<TREETYPE> findItem(T item)
        Description copied from interface: ITreeNode
        This method traverses the tree and searches for the passed item passed. The passed argument identifies the item that should be found. If a node is found, the return value is the treenode, otherwise it is null. The comparison between the passed item and the current node is based on the method ITreeNode.checkItem(T). The method itself contains a typeparameter T which makes the passed argument generic. This typeparameter is replaced with the specific type during method call.
        Specified by:
        findItem in interface ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the passed item
        Parameters:
        item - The specific item that we try to find
        Returns:
        the treenode if found, or null if it can't be found

      • checkItem

        public <T> boolean checkItem(T item)
        Description copied from interface: ITreeNode
        This method checks the current node against a passed item. If the passed item matches the current node (e.g. the node is the same as the item or the underlying property of the node is equal to the passed item) then true is returned. Otherwise false is returned. The type of the item is determined during the method call and thus a typeparameter is used.
        Specified by:
        checkItem in interface ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the passed item
        Parameters:
        item - The specific item that is checked
        Returns:
        true if the passed item is matching the current node, false otherwise
